  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients receiving BNP or nitroglycerin (IV) during the angioplasty procedure. 24 h after the
      procedure, vascular reactivity will be re-examined using the brachial artery flow-mediated
      dilatation study. Blood assays for ET-1, pro-BNP, and various inflammatory markers will be
      checked before and 24 h after the procedure. It is our hypothesis that endothelial function
      will be better in the BNP treated patients compared to the NTG treated patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
